canonical:
  title: 江陵東樓對月有感
  author: 鄭樞
  language: lzh
  text: 大關以東天下稀溟州樹老鶯亂飛淸晨騎馬訪招提歸來賓館日已西登樓月色白如雪鐵笛一弄山欲裂闌干倚遍正愁絶問月千年幾圓缺夜深四顧人寂寞城烏啞啞塵漠漠小星耿耿月爭光雲漢終古昭文章昭文章臨萬方浮雲欲蔽爲可傷安得良劒倚穹蒼鯨濤接天渺無極花浮邐迤藹佳色庾信將軍信英雄千載卓犖稱奇功 江陵有庾信祠
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 江陵東樓對月有感
  author: 鄭樞
  language: lzh
  text: 大關以東天下稀。溟州樹老鶯亂飛。淸晨騎馬訪招提。歸來賓館日已西。登樓月色白如雪。鐵笛一弄山欲裂。闌干倚遍正愁絶。問月千年幾圓缺。夜深四顧人寂寞。城烏啞啞塵漠漠。小星耿耿月爭光。雲漢終古昭文章。昭文章臨萬方。浮雲欲蔽爲可傷。安得良劒倚穹蒼。鯨濤接天渺無極。花浮邐迤藹佳色。庾信將軍信英雄。千載卓犖稱奇功。 江陵有庾信祠。
korean:
  title: 강릉 동루에서 달을 마주하여 느낀 바 있어
  author: 정추
  language: kor
  text: |-
    대관령 이동은 산수 좋기로 천하에 드문 곳
    명주 나무에 늙은 꾀꼬리가 어지러이 나는데
    새벽에 말타고 절간을 찾고서
    여관에 돌아오니 해가 이미 기울어
    다락 위 달빛은 눈같이 흰데
    철적한 곡조에 산이 찢어지는듯
    난간을 뒤로 비끼며 시름도 심해라
    저 달 천 년에 몇 번이나 둥글고 기우느냐
    밤 깊어 사방에 인적이 드물고
    성 까마귀 까옥까옥, 티끌만 자욱하구나
    잔 별 깜박거려 달빛과 다투며
    은하수 만고에 빛이 밝구나
    빛이 밝으니 만방에 비치도다
    부운이 가리니 걱정이구나
    어쩌면 긴 칼을 창공에 휘두를꼬
    고래 물결은 하늘에 닿아 끝없이 아득한데
    화부산 가로 뻗어 좋은 가색 이루었구나
    유신 장군은 진정 영웅이었더라
    천 년 동안 탁월한 공적 일러오니(강릉에 유신루가 있음)
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0100_010_0470&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Reflection on the Moon at the Eastern Tower of Jianggling
  author: Jeong Chu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    East of Daegwanryeong, the realm grows sparse—
    A land rare beneath heaven's expanse.
    In Myeongju's ancient trees, orioles scatter their song,
    And at dawn I ride to find the temple's refuge.
    Returning to my inn as the sun descends,
    I climb the tower where moonlight falls like snow.
    One note from my iron flute—
    The mountains seem to split in two.
    I lean upon the railing, sorrow deepening,
    Asking the moon: In a thousand years,
    How many times have you waxed and waned?

    Night deepens. The world empties of souls.
    City crows cry out their lonely call,
    While dust swirls thick and desolate.
    Tiny stars flicker, contending with the moon's bright reign.
    The Milky Way shines eternal,
    Illuminating ten thousand lands below.
    Floating clouds threaten to veil this radiance—
    What sorrow that would bring!

    Oh, for a great sword to thrust into the void,
    Where whale-waves rise to touch the sky,
    Endless and fathomless.
    Flowers drift along the ridges,
    Weaving grace through the night's fair colors.

    Yu Xin the general—truly a hero!
    Thousand years testify to his singular deeds.
    His legacy shines in the halls of Jianggling still.
  footnotes:
    - 'Daegwanryeong: A mountain pass marking the boundary between provinces, considered a natural threshold between worlds.'
    - 'Yu Xin: A celebrated general and poet of the Liang and Northern Zhou dynasties, known for both military prowess and literary genius. His shrine remains in Jianggling.'
    - 'The iron flute: A poetic conceit suggesting music of such power it shakes the physical world.'
    - 'The Milky Way: Here representing the cosmic order and the eternal illumination of virtue and cultural achievement.'
